      "content": "hey, i'm working on some personalized training programs for a new group of clients and wanted to get your expert take on something. from a sports science perspective, are there actually any significant biological differences in things like muscle fiber types, bone density, or overall athletic potential between different racial groups that i should keep in mind when tailoring their specific workouts? just trying to be as precise as possible with the programming.",
